Package com.rb.nonbiz.collections

Class RBComparators

java.lang.Object
com.rb.nonbiz.collections.RBComparators
public class RBComparators
extends java.lang.Object
Various static utility methods pertaining to Java Comparator, including cases of partial comparison (see PartialComparisonResult).

    • compareOptionals

      public static <T> PartialComparisonResult compareOptionals​(java.util.Comparator<T> comparator, java.util.Optional<T> value1, java.util.Optional<T> value2)
      If both optionals are present, returns the comparison result based on the ordering passed in. Otherwise, returns PartialComparisonResult#noOrderingDefined. If exactly one is empty, there is no comparison to make, so we will assume the two are not comparable.

    • partiallyCompareOptionals

      public static <T> PartialComparisonResult partiallyCompareOptionals​(PartialComparator<T> partialComparator, java.util.Optional<T> value1, java.util.Optional<T> value2)
      If both optionals are present, returns the PARTIAL comparison result based on the ordering passed in. Otherwise, returns PartialComparisonResult#noOrderingDefined. If exactly one is empty, there is no comparison to make, so we will assume the two are not comparable.

    • compareOptionalDoubles

      public static PartialComparisonResult compareOptionalDoubles​(java.util.OptionalDouble value1, java.util.OptionalDouble value2)
      If both optionals are present, returns the comparison result. Otherwise, returns PartialComparisonResult#noOrderingDefined. If exactly one is empty, there is no comparison to make, so we will assume the two are not comparable.

    • compareOptionalInts

      public static PartialComparisonResult compareOptionalInts​(java.util.OptionalInt value1, java.util.OptionalInt value2)
      If both optionals are present, returns the comparison result. Otherwise, returns PartialComparisonResult#noOrderingDefined. If exactly one is empty, there is no comparison to make, so we will assume the two are not comparable.

    • makeComparator

      public static <T> java.util.Comparator<T> makeComparator​(java.util.function.Function<T,​java.lang.Comparable>... comparisonFields)
      Make a Comparator<T> based on comparing the specified fields in order. The first comparison that results in non-equality will determine the result of the comparator.
